      <hedline>
        <hl1>Through Rose-Colored Glass</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Mallery Lane</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rose-colored glass front of Commes des Garcons perfume shop in Paris exemplifies new emphasis on design in city's shopfronts; photo (S) (Currents)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Paris shopfronts are becoming more design conscious. Future Systems, the avant-garde British architecture firm, laminated plastic film onto glass to add a rosy glow to the 19th-century stone facade of the recently opened Comme des Garcons perfume shop, at 23 Place du Marche-St.-Honore.</p>
      </block>
